Bring a large #saucepan{} of water to the boil with @salt{1/4%tsp} for the rice.

When boiling, add the @Jasmine Rice{150} and cook for ~{12%mins}.

Drain in a #sieve{}, pop back in the pan, cover with a #lid{} and leave to the
side until ready to serve.

Meanwhile, peel and grate the @Garlic Clove{2}(peeled and grated) (or use a
#garlic press{}).

Trim and thinly slice the @Spring Onion{1}(trimmed and thinly sliced).

Drain the @Firm Tofu{280} and chop into 2cm cubes. Pat dry with
#kitchen paper{}.

Add the @Cornflour{10%g} to a #bowl{}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Toss
the tofu into the flour and mix until fully coated.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} in a large #frying pan{} on high heat.

Once hot, add the tofu pieces to the pan. Fry until crispy, ~{6-8%mins}.

Carefully turn every 1-2 mins to ensure they don't burn.

When ready, transfer the tofu to a #plate{} lined with kitchen paper.

Pop the now empty pan back on high heat with a drizzle of oil. Add the
@Sliced Mushrooms{180}, season with salt and pepper and cook until browned,
~{3-4%mins}, stirring occasionally.

Meanwhile, in a bowl, mix together the garlic, @Miso Paste{15%g},
@Soy Sauce{15%ml}, @Szechuan Paste{75%g}, @Water for the Sauce{50%ml} and
@Sugar{2%g}.

Pour the sauce into the pan. Bring to the boil, then lower the heat to medium.

Next, return the tofu to the pan with the sauce, stir to coat.

Add the @Baby Spinach{100} into the pan a handful at a time until wilted and
piping hot, ~{1-2%mins}.

Remove from the heat.

> TIP: Add a splash of water too if the sauce has thickened too much.

Fluff up the rice with a #fork{}.

Serve the rice in #bowls{}, with the mushroom mapo tofu on top. Make sure to
get all of the sauce.

Scatter the spring onions on top. Enjoy!